header.gameNote: LAS VEGAS CLASSIC AT LAS VEGAS NV

article.headline: Wagner 69, Jackson St. 62
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Chris Martin scored a game-high 27 points to lead Wagner over Jackson State 71-62 in the third round of the Las Vegas Classic on Tuesday night. Martin, who had three steals, was 11 of 12 from the free-throw line. Ryan Conrad added 13 points for the Seahawks (2-9). Tyrone Hanson led Jackson State (0-10) with 19 points and six rebounds. Rod Melvin had 10 points for the Tigers. Wagner led for most of the first half and took a 33-27 halftime lead. The Seahawks pulled away in the second half, building three 13-point leads. Both teams play on Wednesday afternoon in the final round. This was Wagner's first win of the four-game tournament.
